Usage: ALARM [LIST|KILL|POP <id>|PUSH <minutes> <command>] 
   It performs one or many commands when their triggers are matched
   every X minutes. eg.

   To execute "/SAY hi" every 5 minutes:
                               /ALARM PUSH 5 hi

   To execute "/ECHO *wake up*" every minute:
                        /ALARM PUSH 1 /ECHO *wake up*

   To list all the scheduled alarms:
                                 /ALARM LIST

   This will display all the active alarms with their proper id.
   To remove the first example alarm:
                            /ALARM POP <alarm id>

   To kill all alarm events:
                                 /ALARM KILL

